        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 1:44PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pat Mayse Lake, or 14 miles northwest of Paris, moving southeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Camp Maxey, Sumner, and Pat Mayse Lake around 150 PM CDT.
Paris and Lake Crook around 155 PM CDT.
Reno around 210 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include East Direct,
Monkstown, Toco, Noble, Forest Chapel, Garretts Bluff, Direct, Allens
Point, Midcity, and Forest Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
